CPV_INTRO: Common Procurement Vocabulary (CPV) codes are a framework of classification for public procurement that makes use of a standardized vocabulary. With the aid of CPV codes, procurement staff may consistently classify their contract notices and make it simpler for suppliers and contracting authorities to locate notices. The vocabulary is built on a tree structure comprising codes up to 9 digits which is a 8 digit code with a verification digit that are linked to terminology that defines the kind of goods or services that the contract is for.
HOW_TO_UPDATE_CPV_CODES_R1: The CPV Codes displays according to the hierarchy in selected language (Default language would be logged in language)
HOW_TO_UPDATE_CPV_CODES_R2: Using "+," make the codes expanded to discover your precise business domain, and "-," make them unfold.
HOW_TO_UPDATE_CPV_CODES_R3: Check all the boxes to choose the codes that apply to your business domain.
HOW_TO_UPDATE_CPV_CODES_R4: You may uncheck/remove the unintended codes.
HOW_TO_UPDATE_CPV_CODES_R5: To save your work, choose "Update". The CPV Codes will be saved in selected Language.(Do a new update if you want to include a different language.)
WARNING_LOOSE_CHANGES: Changes that you made may not be saved.
NACE_INTRO: The comprehensive classification system for goods and economic activities is referred to as NACE, or Nomenclature of Economic Activities. They divide up the variety of economic activities so that one can relate a statistical unit to the activity a certain NACE code denotes. NACE employs four levels of hierarchy.
WHY_UPDATE_NACE_CODES_REASON: Your company will be listed on the "Star Search Engine," which is also a global standard.
HOW_TO_UPDATE_NACE_CODES: How to update your NACE Codes?

HOW_TO_UPDATE_NACE_CODES_R3: Check all the boxes to choose the codes that apply to your business domain.

UNSPSC_INTRO: The United Nations Standard Products and Services Code (UNSPSC) is a taxonomy of products and services was created to cater to the many demands of organizations and corporations engaged in the global trade, analysis, and regulation of goods and services. It is an eight-digit number that represents a four-level structure.

MARKET_INTRO: The markets are a good way to find your business in a location wise. You can update the locations of your business here. The locations can be saved according to your country’s administrative divisions. As an example, Norway has Counties, Regions and Municipalities.
WHY_UPDATE_MARKET_REASON: Your company will be listed on the "Star Search Engine," according to the market views you save, So that the others can know that your business is out there in their locations.
HOW_TO_UPDATE_MARKET_R1: First, you have to select your country from the dropdown.
HOW_TO_UPDATE_MARKET_R2: Then you can select values from dropdowns allocated according to the selected country.
HOW_TO_UPDATE_MARKET_R3: According to the previously selected dropdown, the rest of the dropdowns will be drilled down.
HOW_TO_UPDATE_MARKET_R4: You may remove markets by selecting “X” at the municipality level.
HOW_TO_UPDATE_MARKET_R5: To save your work, choose "Update". The Markets will be saved and you can view them.
